The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	Pacer Nilkantha Das picked up five wickets to help Bengal beat Karnataka by 31 runs in a CK Nayudu Trophy quarter final match at the Eden Gardens.       
	Brief Scores: Bengal 219 amp; 109 vs Karnataka 141 amp; 156 (N Das 5/60). Bengal won by 31 runs.          
	 Avik Mallick replaced Arindam Ghosh in the Bengal squad for the Ranji Trophy Plate Group match against Vidarbha, which will start on Friday in Nagpur.           
	 Mahadevi Birla High School beat Loreto Bowbazar while Modern HS defeated La Martiniere to reach the girls final of the 12th Inter-School tennis Championship organised by ITA at SAI Complex (Eastern centre).           
	 Interkraft beat Cognizant Technologies while CESC A beat Transafe Services Ltd in the Transafe Merchants Cup tennis meet at the South Club on Monday.                
	Football: Fed Cup, United SC vs SBT; Dempo vs Mumbai FC. At Barasat Stadium from 3:15 pm.                                                                                                                                                                      
